Python is a high -level, interpreted programming language used for web development, data 
science, and automation.   
It supports multiple paradigms like procedural, object -oriented, and functional 
programming.   
Lists in Python are mutable, while tuples are immutable.   
Dictionaries in Python store data as key -value pairs.   
Functions in Python are defined using the def keyword.   
Classes and objects enable object -oriented programming in Python.   
Decorators allow modification of function behavior without changing the function code.   
Generators yield values one at a time using the yield keyword.

Python is a high -level, interpreted programming language. It was created by Guido van Rossum in 1991. Python is known for its simplicity and readability.

Python supports multiple paradigms: - Procedural programming - Object -oriented programming - Functional programming Lists in Python are mutable, while tuples are immutable. Dictionaries in Python store data as key -value pairs.

Functions in Python are defined using the def keyword. Classes and objects enable object -oriented programming in Python. Decorators allow modification of function behavior without changing the function code. Generators yield values one at a time using the yield keyword.
